# Python APIs to request data from STIX data server.

An example is given as below


```python
from stix import api
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
%matplotlib notebook
```


```python
res= api.fetch('2020-06-21T18:00:00','2020-06-21T23:30:00','lc')
#res.info()
```

    Fetching data: 100%|██████████| 273k/273k [00:00<00:00, 934kiB/s] 



```python
data=res[1].data
```


```python
lc_data=data['COUNTS'].transpose()

t=[4*x for x in range(len(lc_data[0]))]
```


```python
for i in range(5):
    plt.plot(t, lc_data[i])
plt.xlabel('Time (s)')
plt.ylabel('Counts')
plt.title('STIX light curves')
```
